      <div class="gbm-body">
        <p>
          MeowlWatch&apos;s main use case is for students to check their remaining meal plan balances through the app, after signing in once.
          This was accomplished by polling the web version of the balance check page on Northwestern Dining&apos;s own website, using NetID credentials that are securely stored on the user&apos;s device.
          At the time of writing, it appears that Northwestern Dining has permanently taken down this feature on their website entirely, meaning MeowlWatch will no longer be able to provide the balance check feature either.
          I am no longer able to provide a meaningful app experience without this essential feature.
          This, coupled with the recent closure of campus facilities, and the apparent direction of NU Dining&apos;s long-term plans, has led me to discontinue the app.
        </p>
        <p>
          The rest of this post tells the story behind the app, as a goodbye to this project that&apos;s become associated with my own journey at Northwestern. Perhaps its story can help you with your own project, too.
        </p>
