        <h3>Looking back üëÄ</h3>
        <p>
          I never expected it to get this far, at all.
          The way the app pulled meal balance data is undocumented at best, and unauthorised at worst.
          At one point, I tried to get Northwestern Dining to at least help me advertise the app, but that discussion didn&apos;t go anywhere.
          I half-expected an inevitable strongly-worded letter from someone about unauthorised use of the school network, considering a good amount of traffic to their server would have been from my users.
          That letter never came, though, to my relief.
        </p>
        <p>
          Maybe at some point someone developed a routine to check their Equivalency balance every week before they expired.
          Maybe someone got crazy tipsy but still had their wits together to check on their points before buying out the chips and salsa shelf at Lisa&apos;s.
          I&apos;ll never know, but I sincerely hope that this app has been useful to someone out there.
          If you have a story, <LinkTo @route="index">let me know</LinkTo>! I&apos;d love to hear it.
        </p>

