        <h3>Technical FAQ ü§ì</h3>
        <p><em>How did you pull user data from Northwestern?</em></p>
        <p>
          On the web page, the browser makes a series of HTTP GET/POST requests to take the user through the NUIT SSO flow.
          All I did was step through it, mimic it with code, and then parse the response into the app.
          So, yes, probably against their TOS.
          I suspect this approach won&apos;t work anymore if Northwestern ups their security, like with MFA, so future projects like this should definitely check in with NUIT first.
        </p>

        <p><em>How much money did you make from this?</em></p>
        <p>
          Net loss.
          It costs $100 per year to host stuff on the App Store, ad revenue and tips couldn&apos;t make up for it, and I couldn&apos;t be bothered to look for other revenue streams.
          I did have entrepreneurial plans at first, but I made it closer to a public utility as time went on.
          I kept it up for as long as people were using it :)
        </p>

